@node INSTALLATIONE "Installation"

@{b}Installation@{ub}

   Copy "WW-Labels.rexx" in the drawer WWRexx. Then you go to "ARexx-Macro" in
   the Wordworth-menu "Extras", click on "new" and then on "WW-Labels.rexx", of course.
   Now you can start it by another double-click.




@endnode
@node USEAGE "Useage"

   Well, just try it: Start it from within Wordworth and watch what it does: It draws
   Textboxes, yeah! (At least it should do that...)
   If you want to alter height, upper or lower margin, number of boxes etc, then load
   WW.Labels.rexx with a text editor or with Wordworth, change everything (it should
   be self-explaining) and save it again (as ASCII)
   I will make a version with requesters only if you contact me. I don't need that
   myself.


@endnode
